@92 = ~Yes, my furry friend. You are absolutely right. It is unfair that bears cannot be bards, although many of them are quite talented. ~
@93 = ~I think the audience is simply not ready yet to appreciate the talent of the bear poet without prejudice due to his formidable appearance and voice. But in the future, anything is possible. ~
@94 = ~Sniff-sniff...~
@95 = ~I don't think you should try this now, Wilson. Try reading your poems to me first! The brave Sir Garrick will assess your abilities impartially and tell you if they are ready to be presented to the public.~ [GARRICKK]
@96 = ~Wff... Rff...! Sniff. Sniff.~
@97 = ~Wrr. Snort. Snuff. Snuff.~
@98 = ~Hmm... You rhymed everything so skillfully as if you were at Waterdeep Bard College. ~
@99 = ~But the metaphors you used do need some more work. Comparison of women's eyes with raspberries does not sound very good, I think. But you are clearly talented, my furry friend!~
@100 = ~Snort, rff!~

@101  = ~Could we stop here for the night? I simply must have a chance to catch up on my annotation.~
