// NEW (v.12)
@253 = ~Garrick... You're a bard from the north, aren't you?~
@254 = ~Yes my lady, and I'm at your service. Although let me guess: You want me to write a poem about you, but you are embarrassed to ask?~ [GARRICKG]
@255 = ~No... I just wanted to get to know you better.~
@256 = ~Oh, that's for the best... Today rhymes don't come to my mind at all, but soon I will begin to create my masterpieces again, and especially if you walk beside me. Even an orc would become a poet at the sight of your beauty.~ [GARRICKO]
@257 = ~Oh! Thanks Garrick... *blushes*~
@258 = ~Korgan, you're from the Underdark, right? ~
@259 = ~How did you guess, jester? Found a book that boosts intelligence?~
@260 = ~Ah, I appreciate your irony and your ability to cross verbal swords, but right now I just wanted to know a thing or two about life underground.~
@261 = ~You wouldn't survive there alone for one day, being a weakling and such. The monsters from the Underdark would eat you for breakfast, and that is if they felt like being nice.~
@262 = ~I doubt they would be interested in me - I'm so slim and graceful that there is almost no meat on my bones, but based on what you said, I would rather not get to know them and not check it out.~
@263 = ~I was actually wondering something else: How do the dwarven underground cities have fun? Are there theaters, musicians, dinner parties? What kind of poetry is in vogue with dwarven bards? Perhaps battle poems?~
@264 = ~Yes, we know how to have fun, and we do it the way you surfacers never dreamed of! Your theaters, where the actors grimace on stage to the laughter of the audience, complete nonsense!~
@265 = ~Dwarves don't waste their time with such frivolous entertainment. If we sing songs, we do it in a tavern with a mug of ale in hand. The tavern is like a second home for us - There we communicate with our fellow clan members, play dice and tell stories. Dwarves also love competition - Sparring, tournament fights, gladiator fights and the like.~
@266 = ~I disagree with you, my friend - Every method of relaxation has its own charm. It’s a shame you don’t know how to appreciate exquisite poetry.~
@267 = ~For a dwarf, the best poetry is the clamor of battle and the sound of the hammer in the forge! ~
@268 = ~So then every dwarf is a poet who creates his masterpieces in moments of battle? This is an interesting thought, you need to write this down, it may come in handy.~
@269 = ~You see, I thought of writing a chapter on dwarves in my ballad on Brave Sir Garrick, but the problem is that I have never been to your cities and the public can catch me cheating. ~
@270 = ~So I want to know more about your customs, and I would be honored to have you be my consultant.~ [GARRICKY]
@271 = ~I've no time to be bothered about poetry this or poems that, go and bother someone else, ye fool!~

// NEW (v.12.6)
// Valygar - Garrick
@272 = ~Valygar, you're thinking about something bad again. ~
@273 = ~Is it that noticeable?~
@274 = ~Of course, you are gloomy and your lips are tightly compressed. But listen to me... you, of course, have something to grieve about, no one argues, but don’t harass yourself like that.~
@275 = ~The sun is still shining on us, and the birds are chirping just as loudly, and the foliage is rustling in the wind, as if singing a kind song. This world lives and breathes, and tries to please you somehow. Just try and smile back at it.~
@276 = ~Strange, you say platitudes that I would disdain at any other time... but somehow they make sense in your mouth. Maybe because you yourself live like a bird or a leaf in the wind. You are a sunny guy full of life. And this is perhaps contagious.~ [GARRICKH]
@277 = ~Oh, to hear that from you, Valygar... I'm glad if I could dispel your gloomy mood even a little.~
@278 = ~*smiles* You did, you did. That is why the gods send us bards. You're doing your job well, Garrick. I wish you the best of luck.~

// Nalia-Garrick 1 (in the castle)
@279 = ~Wow, what a castle! Large and ancient, full of mysterious echoes of the past. Family portraits, antique furniture and forgotten secrets! How lovely. ~
@280 = ~Garrick... ~
@281 = ~Bookcases keep yellowed scrolls and tomes in worn bindings, and they contain legends, sagas, ballads... ramshackle pages...~
@282 = ~Garrick, stop, stop. You're getting too carried away. Although, yes, you're right, our castle has all this and more, but now is not the time for that!~
@283 = ~I know, I know. The castle has been captured by the enemy, and we are once again experiencing the most dangerous adventure! Don't worry, Nalia! After all, the great hero <CHARNAME> and the valiant Sir Garrick are with you. We will not let anyone offend you or your house. Trust me.~
@284 = ~I believe you Garrick, thanks for the kind words, but now let's hurry, no matter what you say, my heart is beating with anxious anticipation...~
@285 = ~Of course. Let's go!~ [GARRICKA]

// Nalia-Garrick 2 (after freeing the castle)
@286 = ~Garrick, you're looking at me like that... Let me guess. Would you like to share with me your sublime thoughts inspired by the beauties of nature? Or are they the poetic fruits of bardic inspiration?~
@287 = ~No... Yes... That is, I wanted to say... again, all the words escaped out of my head, like when Cyrando... ugh! It's better not to think about it.~
@288 = ~It's just, Nalia, I just want to say that I sympathize with you. I am very sorry that you had to go through such an ordeal. ~
@289 = ~*Excited* Garrick...~
@290 = ~No, wait. You see, I always thought that a lady in trouble was a very intriguing plot. Terrible trials, insidious enemies, noble saviors - this is great material, the audience is delighted with such stories. Well, and I'm glad, of course, that we helped you...~
@291 = ~But I can see how frail you are... how nervous you are. So I would prefer that this never happened to you. I don't want such plots for my ballads. Not at this price. That's all.~
@292 = ~*Smiling* Thank you. And yet, brave Sir Garrick, I am grateful that you were among those who helped me in difficult times. I will try to forget about the bad, and remember the good with pleasure. ~
@293 = ~And am I one of the... good?~
@294 = ~Of course!~
@295 = ~Oh, I'm so happy! You inspired me, my lady, the first lines of the verse came by themselves!.. So where is my quill?~

// Nalia-Garrick 3
@297 = ~*Hums a funny song to himself*~
@298 = ~Garrick! What... what are you singing? ~
@299 = ~Ah... I learned this song in Baldur's Gate, it's about the founder of this city, the brave captain Balduran. Everyone there knows him.~
@300 = ~Yes! Of course I remembered. I was still little when guests came to us from Brother Baldur. And one of them sang this song, paying tribute to the ancient wine from our cellars. Hee-hee... He repeated it several times, I memorized a couple of verses, and then I walked around and sang at the top of my voice. How angry my aunt was! She was terrified that a young lady sang something like that. It was not at all befitting a girl of noble blood.~
@301 = ~These songs are the best! They strengthen and cheer up the spirit... they just make it fun.~
@302 = ~*Squinting slyly* I knew it, Garrick. Even though you've been studying a volume of high elven poetry every day, songs like these are much closer to your heart.~
@303 = ~*Embarrassed* Nalia... I... just...~
@304 = ~Oh, don't be embarrassed. This is great. You are who you are. Stay that way.~
@305 = ~You know what? Let's sing this song together!~
@306 = ~Of course, come on! How does it start again...? Remind me. *Singing along with Garrick*~
@307 = ~Thank you, Nalia. My how your eyes are shining...Just now when you were singing, you were so beautiful...!~ [GARRICK4]
@308 = ~Er, no, I’m not saying that while you’re not singing, you’re ugly... very much... just art...it transforms... and anyway... no, you and the truth is always beautiful!~
@309 = ~*Laughs* Oh, don't start... ~
@310 = ~I am silent. I'd better try to compose a funny song myself. For you, Nalia. ~

// Nalia-Garrick 4
@311 = ~Garrick, what are these?~
@312 = ~These are... well... daisies. Flowers.~
@313 = ~We'll leave the botany lesson for later. Just tell me, you're not going to... ~
@314 = ~Give them to you? Indeed I am.~
@315 = ~Garrick, I... ~
@316 = ~No, listen. I admire you. You could be one of those prime young ladies... eventually become your aunt Delcia. But instead you walk with us, expose yourself to danger and inconvenience, sometimes you spend the night under the open sky and eat whatever you have to. Because this is... freedom? Yes?~
@317 = ~Yes, my dear poet. You guessed it right.~
@318 = ~I love... people like you. You have a spirit of adventure, a spirit of a bard... even though you don't write poetry. Even then, I wanted to... Come on. Just take it. Please.~ [GARRICKU]
@319 = ~*Accepting the flowers* Thank you, Garrick. I am very pleased, really. It's good to be understood.~
@320 = ~Nalia, come forth, you and me... and, you don't need to say anything else. Although, we'd better get going, because <CHARNAME> is already looking at us in a strange way.~

// Nalia-Garrick 5
@321 = ~Nalia... You know... I wrote something here. Do you want to take a look? Actually, it was written for you... and about you. So only you just need to read it!~
@322 = ~What an intriguing foreword, Garrick. Of course I want to read this! ~
@323 = ~*Visibly agitated, hands out a piece of paper to Nalia*~
@324 = ~Hmm... Yeah... Wow... Garrick, I don't even know what to say. ~
@325 = ~Do you not like it?~
@326 = ~You see, when poetry is dedicated to you, it's too pleasant and exciting to immediately begin to sort it out line by line and criticize. So first, I'll just say thank you from the bottom of my heart. But then...~
@327 = ~(Sadly) So you didn't like it after all?~
@328 = ~Garrick... dear Garrick, you don't have to practice these lush and banal comparisons! Especially, what are “eye like a diamond, lips like a coral”... this is not your style. And... it's not about me. I am not like this. It would be much more interesting to listen to the funny song that you promised to compose for me.~
@329 = ~I'll write it! I will compose a song for you in which there will be laughter in every line! I promise. But, Nalia... I don't know how to say... ~
@330 = ~Just say it as it is. How you think and feel. ~
@331 = ~Then... You are the best, Nalia! I am so glad that you are now in my life, and I want it to be that way forever.~
@332 = ~Garrick... You see how easy it is... But also how difficult it can be at the same time, yes? I understand. I am also very glad that fate brought us together.~
@333 = ~So can I really hope... for... more? ~
@334 = ~Of course you fool. Haven't you figured it out yet?~
@335 = ~*Kisses Nalia on the cheek* So we'll continue this conversation later, right?~
@336 = ~I'm sure of it. ~

// Nalia-Garrick 6
@337 = ~Nalia... sweet Nalia, what's wrong with you? Are you crying?~
@338 = ~No, I just suddenly felt very sad. I do not know why. Not that I miss home... not at all. The former life does not attract me at all. But now I am in the shadow of <CHARNAME>, and this will not always be the case. So when the time comes, where will I go? Which road is mine? What am I even like?~
@339 = ~Although this might be silly reasoning, because tomorrow we could be killed in a serious skirmish...~
@340 = ~Oh, don't think about such things! You're just tired. Or maybe... are you lonely? But there is me! And I'm always here.~
@341 = ~I know, Garrick, dear, I know. And believe me, I really appreciate it.~
@342 = ~And I wrote a “laughing” song for you as I promised. But now is probably not the time...~ [GARRICKQ]
@343 = ~(Nalia livens up a bit) It's always time!~
@344 = ~Yes? Okay this is great! Then... listen.~
@345 = ~When the green woods laugh with the voice of joy,
And the dimpling stream runs laughing by;
When the air does laugh with our merry wit,
And the green hill laughs with the noise of it;~
@346 = ~When the meadows laugh with lively green,
And the grasshopper laughs in the merry scene,
When Mary and Susan and Emily
With their sweet round mouths sing 'Ha, Ha, He!'~
@347 = ~When the painted birds laugh in the shade,
Where our table with cherries and nuts is spread,
Come live, and be merry, and join with me,
To sing the sweet chorus of 'Ha, Ha, He!'~
@348 = ~You... have dispelled my causeless sadness, Garrick...~
@349 = ~*Nalia comes close to Garrick, he leans towards her, and their lips touch*~
@350 = ~*Whispering* Did you like the song?~
@351 = ~Yes. And I will never be sad again when you are around. ~
@352 = ~I love you.~
@353 = ~And I love you. Your song has a great ending! ~
@354 = ~Ending? It's just the beginning.~ [GARRICKH]
@355 = ~*Snuggling against Garrick's chest* And that's right! Let's pray to the gods to give us as much time as possible. To be together...~

// Nalia-Garrick 7
@356 = ~Nalia... can I have a minute of your time?~
@357 = ~Of course, my nightingale, what do you want? ~
@358 = ~Look... I found this. Maybe it will come in handy. Once upon a time, after all, you were fond of rogue art. ~
@359 = ~A ring...?~
@360 = ~Yes, I checked it carefully, there is no evil magic or trick here. And the enchantment on this ring will help you if you suddenly want to remember the past *Smiles*~
@361 = ~Oh thank you! This is a great gift.~
@362 = ~Is that truly a gift...? I would have thought a gift to be something I bought for you to your liking. However, I can't imagine what that could be...~
@363 = ~Garrick, you're just lovely!~
@364 = ~Nalia... you're not laughing at me, are you? ~
@365 = ~Of course not. *Ruffles his hair* You're so cute! You yourself are the best gift for me. So don't worry.~
@366 = ~And yet... You are indifferent to jewelry, and enchanted things like this ring are more a necessity in our business than a nice gift... ~
@367 = ~Garrick... do you remember the lovely bouquet you gave me?~
@368 = ~*Embarrassed* They were just daisies... You deserve gorgeous roses and orchids!~
@369 = ~No, no. It was the most wonderful bouquet. Unfortunately, it faded, although I dried a few flowers in the book as a keepsake. If you want to give me something, get an unfading bunch of simple wildflowers. That will be the sweetest gift I've ever had.~
@370 = ~Really? That's lovely! I will try, you can be sure of that. *kisses Nalia*~
@371 = ~I don’t doubt or feel sad anymore, even when it’s not easy for me. I'm glad I met you along the way.~
@372 = ~*Smiles* But we have to go. Let's not keep anyone waiting for us!~

// Nalia-Garrick 8 (Underdark)
@373 = ~Garrick... I want to squeeze your hand, but make it so that no one notices. For we are all drow at the moment, and drow do not hold hands.~
@374 = ~This place wafts malice at it's core with the darkness that accompanies it. It makes me want the sun, but it would probably be better not to think about the sun here. It's unbearable. The gloom is everywhere... it seems that now it will shrink around us and suffocate us.~
@375 = ~I also feel uneasy here, but hold on, my darling. Let's remember that sooner or later we'll get out of here safe and sound. And then we will be able to hold hands without fear.~ [GARRICKB]
@376 = ~That's right. I hope we succeed down here with all my might, but I will never forget this eerie place. You see, when I sneaked out of the keep and watched the life of ordinary people, it seemed to me that I had seen enough of all sorts of calamities and injustice. But I couldn't even imagine what we have encountered here.~
@377 = ~This are is just... too cruel. And it is so painful to realize that nothing can be done, nothing can be changed! We are drow while I just want to use my magic and... and...~
@378 = ~Nalia... shhhh... Please calm down. Yes, we can’t do anything here, but we can try to survive, and return to the surface. Once there we can fight injustice and all kinds of evil for as far as we can go, and so it will be done! You have the Gallant Sir Garrick's word!~
@379 = ~You're right. I should be careful not to let anyone down. Garrick, you are my sun, and with you I am brighter in this gloomy darkness. Thank you.~

// Nalia-Garrick 9 (Underdark)
@380 = ~Garrick, while I'm very pleased that you put your arm around my waist, I want to remind you that drow men don't do that! They may become furious for such a liberty and grow highly suspicious of us.~
@381 = ~*Letting go of Nalia* Sorry, I forgot. I always want to hold you.~
@382 = ~Well... to be honest... it's mutual. Although It would be much safer to give you a good slap in the face. It won't surprise anyone here.~
@383 = ~A Slap in the face? To me? What for?~
@384 = ~Who's staring at the female drow? They are pretty and dress quite revealingly, so I’m not surprised that some bard looks at them with their mouth open.~
@385 = ~Sweetheart, you're exaggerating! Of course, such an exotic beauty attracts the eye, but... I don't like their faces. Too much arrogance and overbearing. And their cruelty creeps into those elven features.~
@386 = ~No dear, the bard in me is rather indignant than admiring, so I don't deserve a slap from my beloved. And as you know, you can always trust your handsome man! Even though there may be a lot of women out there, there is only one Nalia, and she's mine! Really.~
@387 = ~True, true. I love you, nightingale. ~
@388 = ~As do I my love. Ah, I'd rather get out of here! I want the sun to light up your face as soon as possible, which I will kiss as long as I want, without looking back at any drow!~

// Nalia-Garrick 10 (Exit from Underdark)
@389 = ~The sky! The sky is over our heads! Praise to all the gods. Sometimes I was beginning to think that I would never see it again.~
@390 = ~Hooray! Just as I said that we would get out of there safe and sound.~
@391 = ~Yes, my sunny love, whose zest for life has not been shaken even by the deadly darkness of the Underdark! And I'm happy that your prediction came true.~
@393 = ~I couldn't possibly be more joyous!~ [GARRICKH]
@394 = ~*Grabs Nalia's hands and kisses her passionately*~
@395 = ~You are crazy! They're looking at us...~
@396 = ~Yes they are, and who cares. I'm tired of pretending and holding myself back. Kiss me, my love.~
@397 = ~If you say so... then hold on! I will prove to you that I missed you as much... with all my heart. *She kisses Garrick fervently.* Although my nightingale, our love will have to wait for now for it is time for us to go.~
@398 = ~Yes, exactly my love. Now that we are out of the Underdark, the world around us is smiling at us once again.~

// Nalia-Garrick 11
@399 = ~This magician, Irenicus, this grim figure... Sometimes it seems to me that his shadow looms somewhere ahead, teasing us and keeping us away. ~
@400 = ~But now <CHARNAME> is getting closer to his goal. Sooner or later, we will fight this Irenicus.~
@401 = ~And I hope we succeed. Oh how I am looking forward to this! For <CHARNAME>, for myself - and you, Garrick.~
@402 = ~To say: We did it! Breathe freely and go on our own path?~
@403 = ~Exactly.~
@404 = ~Together?~
@405 = ~Of course. You are truly dear to me.~
@406 = ~As you are to me. Except I feel uneasy at the thought that we might part ways when <CHARNAME> says goodbye to us and travels his own way.~
@407 = ~We will not part, Garrick. ~
@408 = ~Nalia... You are a noblewoman and a high-flying bird. Maybe you won't want to-~
@409 = ~*Gently puts her hand over his mouth* Not another word. We have already gone through so much and seen so much that the unnecessary was erased... even if it did matter, I only care about you... just you yourself. We're just a man and a woman, and nothing else matters.~
@410 = ~*Garrick silently presses Nalia's hand to his lips and does not let go for a long time. Words are not needed now. After all, even bards have moments when silence becomes more valuable than words*~

// Nalia-Garrick 12
@411 = ~Nalia, I have a surprise for you! Remember when you said that you wanted to receive a bouquet of unfading flowers as a gift? I hope you haven't changed your mind?~
@412 = ~Of course not!~
@413 = ~Well hold on then, because this is for you.~
@414 = ~Oh! What delightful wildflowers... and I sense they have a special magic... Thank you, thank you.~
@415 = ~Do you like them? I collected them myself, and then I made an agreement in secret with one magician and now...~
@416 = ~Wait, so you went to meet this magician when you secretly escaped from us recently? ~
@417 = ~Oh? You noticed?~
@418 = ~Of course, and I even intended to secretly follow you... but then I changed my mind. I didn't want to look genuinely jealous and I trust you.~
@419 = ~Thank you! Trust is also a gift. One of the most valuable I think. ~
@420 = ~Garrick, I promised you something. When we stop to rest... ~
@421 = ~Nalia...~
@422 = ~If you want... If you love me...~
@423 = ~Yes...?~
@424 = ~Then let everything else disappear for a while...~

// Nalia-Garrick 13 (rest)
@425 = ~Nalia, let's get away for a while. Certainly not too far from the camp for some monsters to disturb our privacy. ~
@426 = ~So what does my knight want? ~
@427 = ~That's what my lady ... *Hugs Nalia and starts dancing around her* ~
@428 = ~Wow! I like it. When I was bored at the parties, I did not think that I would ever dance with my loved one in the open air... Thank you. By the way, you dance beautifully. You are very musical. ~
@429 = ~I know that. ~
@430 = ~You're also very humble! ~
@431 = ~Well, now you're teasing me. ~
@432 = ~Just a little bit. Never mind. I'm fine with you, and I don't want to leave here. ~
@433 = ~Let's dance a little more. But then I need to make sure you get a good rest. ~
@441 = ~This is exactly what I need. Truly, we have found each other in this world. ~

// Nalia-Garrick (before the final battle with Bodhi)
@442 = ~Bodhi... I can't tolerate her.~
@443 = ~It's good that she didn't manage to persuade <CHARNAME> to work for her that time. ~
@460 = ~I can't believe she was able to persuade <CHARNAME> to work for her that time. ~
@444 = ~She and her vampires are depriving people of the many wonderful things - the joy of life, love, sunshine! Better to perish than suffer such a fate. Garrick, if you weren’t with me, I wouldn’t have felt this so keenly.~
@445 = ~Don't be afraid my dear! I won't let a single vampire come near you. I'll cover you with myself if need be. Er... I talk too much. I hope you don't consider me a chatterbox?~
@446 = ~No, Garrick. You are a brave young man, and I know that you are capable of protecting me. Just like I could for you, heh heh...~
@447 = ~You're right, my beauty. Do not be afraid. These creatures will not take the sun away from us!~

// NPC reactions to Garrick-Nalia romance
@448 = ~Grr! Ye people are so funny - ya bother with trifles and give each other useless trinkets! We dwarves are much smarter. One of me friends, I remember, brought a moonshine still to me wife - that is a gift! A useful thing in the household, not like your slobbery trinkets, har har!!!~
@449 = ~Korgan, I don't think Nalia would use a moonshine while we're on the road. But when we finish traveling, contact me friends - I can make this, and in your castle Nalia, you will always have the best turnip moonshine in the area! You open a tavern for the poor and you will treat everyone for free - then your subjects will carry you in their arms for joy, like my great-great-uncle Duduvar Jansen. True, he was not worn for joy, but, on the contrary, he was seized and carried out of the tavern until he drank everything alone. And he just wanted to celebrate his son's wedding and drink to the health of the young, and then he got too carried away. Besides, he forgot that the wedding was only a week later... Oh, and then he got in huge trouble with his wife about that!~
@450 = ~Garrick, are you picking a gift for Nalia? There is one thing that is useful in the household and for the trade. A moonshine still! When we finish traveling, I can make one for you - and in your castle Nalia, you will always have the best turnip moonshine in the area! You open a tavern for the poor and you will treat everyone for free - then your subjects will carry you in their arms for joy, like my great-great-uncle Duduvar Jansen. True, he was not worn for joy, but, on the contrary, he was seized and carried out of the tavern until he drank everything alone. And he just wanted to celebrate his son's wedding and drink to the health of the young, and then he got too carried away. Besides, he forgot that the wedding was only a week later... Oh, and then he got in huge trouble with his wife about that!~
@451 = ~Thanks for the offer, Jan. But I would probably refuse. I think it's better not to let the poor get drunk, but to help them live better and feed their families. ~
@452 = ~The best gift for a woman is a sharp sword or dagger! To slice the throats of any idiotic fool!~
@453 = ~Garrick, this be idiocy boy! Ye won't earn much on yer rhymes, but are ye ready to spend yer last coins on a woman?! Ye will never get rich this way!~
@454 = ~*Sigh* (I'm so tired of these monkey's touchy-feely anecdotes!)~

// Nalia-Garrick (Spellhold) 1
@461 = ~Nalia, you know, I feel uncomfortable here anyway, but now it’s not at all good at the thought that if I hadn’t been careful in Athkatla, I could also have come here. Although, of course, I am not as good at magic as you are, but still...~
@462 = ~I'm not a master myself yet. Mother wanted me to study magic, although in Amn they have long looked askance at magicians. But of course we didn't have any problems with the license. What if I was poor but loved magic... would I have ended up here?~
@463 = ~It is unfair that some traitorous sorcerers in the past harassed practitioners of magic so much in those days... While this is a good way to knock out money with licenses, it’s not good for everyone else.~
@464 = ~There is a lot of injustice in Athkatla. But now this city seems so far away... almost unattainable. And, of course, it's much better to be there than here.~
@465 = ~Well, we’ll go back there or we’ll go to a nicer place, we won’t be stuck here forever.~
@466 = ~Ah, Garrick, it's good that even in this dark place, you remain yourself. ~

// Nalia-Garrick (Spellhold) 2
@467 = ~Nalia, how are you? You weren't very scared when <CHARNAME>... became... that... thing!~
@468 = ~Oh, Garrick, of course I was very scared, and who would not be scared? I hope so much that this does not happen again... just a memory makes it creepy.~
@469 = ~Nalia, I...~
@470 = ~Oh no, don't tell me you will protect me if <CHARNAME> transforms again. Run away from him no matter what happens.~
@471 = ~But if he attacks you, I won't run away. I will protect you!~
@472 = ~No Garrick, don't say anything more. I really hope <CHARNAME> can handle this. ~

// Nalia-Garrick (after the quest)
@473 = ~Garrick, Garrick... I still feel uneasy. Just think... I could have lost you! Not in battle, but... but... because of someone else's meanness, greed! No, I can't... ~
@474 = ~Nalia, don't be upset, now everything is in order. Although being separated from you is the most cruel thing that could happen to me. ~
@475 = ~Yes, if you were taken to Calimshan, I would have travelled around it all, even on foot, I would use all the magic available, and I wouldn't stop until I found you!~
@476 = ~Nalia... No one has ever treated me the way you do. ~ [GARRICK4]